President Muhammadu Buhari has urged the Senate to confirm the nomination of Mr. Joe Aniku Michael Ohiani for appointment as substantive Director-General/CEO of the Infrastructure Concession Regulatory Commission. The request was contained in a letter dated 6th June, 2022.   Quick facts about Ekiti 2022 election     I won’t be shocked if social media says I started Boko Haram…     Inflation increases to 17.71% – NBS   The President’s letter was read at plenary by the Senate President, Ahmad Lawan. According to Buhari, the request was in accordance with the provision of Section 22(1)(a) of the Infrastructure Concession Regulatory Commission (Establishment) Act, 2005.